A Mechanism is by definition a Gear, so that you can create new Mechanisms by mixing and matching existing Mechanisms and Gears you have already in your library.

Clockwork include a large library of ready to use Gears to for example do declarative validations, make other Gears asynchronous, and even bind other KEYSTONE components to the Clockwork paradigm.

MvcMailer sends emails using the MVC views as Email Body with no effort. Here's a quick list of features: a) Use Razor/WebForms views b) Use Master pages c) Write Testable Code d) Pass values to your view using ViewBag or ViewModel and e) Generate Absolute URL using Url.Abs method and f) create multi-part emails by just adding a view file, g) scaffold your mailers.
MvcMailer has a MailerBase class that extends ControllerBase class. So, Mailers are just like your Controllers. As a result, you can use all the controller goodies without any learning curve, period. The end result is a professional looking HTML email body ready for your to send to your website users.
Visit the Project site for a comprehensive tutorial on MvcMailer. This version is for ASP.Net MVC 4.5. For other versions, please check MvcMailer4 and MvcMailer3 packages.

description:
ChemBytes Draw is a compact .NET component allowing developers to integrate advanced chemical drawing and chemical information processing into any  .NET project (WPF or Windows Forms).

This is a 30 day evaluation version, which later can be unlocked. No registration required.

As part of a .NET application, ChemBytes Draw on demand displays a fully featured chemical drawing editor, which also supports organometallic, polymer and peptide drawing. Content can be imported from other third party chemical drawing tools, e.g. ISIS/Symyx/Accelrys Draw, ChemDraw, Marvin, etc., via MDL clipboard content or via MDL format export files, including V3000 format. When the user closes the editor, the API takes over and exposes the chemical information for use by your own application. Thus, the molecular weights and elemental formulas of all entered reactants and products, their InChIKeys, bitmap and vector images, bounding boxes, the MDL reaction and molfiles, and the internal XML file format for database storage, etc. are available for further processing. ChemBytes Draw is written in 100% managed code, i.e. it is no wrapper around an existing Java or C++ functionality.

A sample Visual Studio project and sample files are available from the project site.
summary: ChemBytes Draw is a .NET component allowing developers to integrate advanced chemical drawing and chemical information processing into any .NET project (WPF or Windows Forms).
